To enable select and copy functionality in a Fyne `Entry` widget, you can add a context menu with a "Copy" option. Here's an example:

```go
import (
    "github.com/fyne-io/fyne/v2"
    "github.com/fyne-io/fyne/v2/container"
    "github.com/fyne-io/fyne/v2/layout"
    "github.com/fyne-io/fyne/v2/widget"
)

func main() {
    // create an Entry widget
    entry := widget.NewEntry()

    // add context menu with a "Copy" option
    entryMenu := fyne.NewMenu("Copy", fyne.NewMenuItem("Copy", func() {
        clipboard := fyne.CurrentApp().Driver().Clipboard()
        clipboard.SetContent(entry.Text)
    }))
    entry.ContextMenu = fyne.NewMenu("Edit", entryMenu)

    // create a container for the Entry widget and add it to the canvas
    content := container.New(layout.NewHBoxLayout(), entry)
    win := fyne.NewWindow("Entry Widget")
    win.SetContent(content)
    win.ShowAndRun()
}
```

In this example, when the user right-clicks on the Entry widget, a context menu is displayed with a "Copy" option. When the user selects this option, the text in the Entry widget is copied to the clipboard.

